Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{12%ounce} on a diagonal into 1⁄2-inch-thick pieces.
Cut @potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges.

Toss carrots on one side of a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Toss potatoes on empty side with a drizzle of oil, salt,
and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> TIP: If you added any other items to your meal (apps, sides, and/or dessert),
> you can get started on them now!

While veggies roast, cut @broccoli{1} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Halve,
core, and thinly slice @apple{1}.

Halve and toast @demi-baguette{1}; halve crosswise and slice into 1-inch pieces.

Place broccoli in a large #microwave-safe bowl{}; cover tightly with #plastic
wrap{} and poke a few holes in wrap. Microwave until broccoli is tender,
~{1-2%minutes}, tossing halfway through. Carefully uncover (watch out for
steam!) and toss broccoli with salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, heat @cream sauce base{8%ounce}, @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce},
and @water{2%tbsp} (4 TBSP for 4 servings) in a small #pot{} over medium-high
heat until steaming and slightly bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium. Add @white cheddar cheese{1%cup} and @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}
one small handful at a time, alternating and whisking constantly between
additions, until melted.

Arrange potatoes, carrots, broccoli, apple slices, and baguette pieces on a
large #board{} or #platter{}. Serve family style with fondue for dipping.

> TIP: Place a trivet or kitchen towel underneath the fondue pot to protect
> your surface.